notes about image export support in SIMPLE

Goal:  to enable writing simple_image class to PNG or JPG formatted images

Implementation 1: PNM (J Burkardt's libraries)

Pros -- stable fortran code, support for PBM, PGM, and PPM
Cons -- no direct support for PNG or JPG (could use imagemagick to convert)

        Completed -- Yes, simple_pnm.f90

Implementation 2: LibGD

Pros -- support for xpm,ppm, png (libpng) jpeg (libjpeg), tiff (libtiff)
Cons -- lots of dependent libraries, C interface

        Completed -- Partial, simple_img.f90, cgd.c


Implementation 3: Jutils wrapper to libjpeg

Pros -- support for jpeg (libjpeg)
Cons -- lots of dependent libraries, C interface

       Completed -- Partial, older code in simple_jpg.f90, cjpg.c


Implementation 4: STB image

Pros -- PNG and JPG support (+ TGA,BMP,PSD,GIF,PNM),  single c file, public domain, no library dependencies
Cons -- no 12-bit JPG support

        Completed -- Yes, simple_jpg.f90, stb_image*.c/h
